{"type":"message","id":"68e940a4","parentId":"53a9202e","timestamp":"2026-02-17T23:00:00.165Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:10a19bb7-7afb-4b24-8478-62555b540c2d daily-ping-telegram] Send the daily ping to Telegram (ID: 1087368827). Fetch: 1) Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API (https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true), 2) Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance, 3) Top 5 GitHub repos by stars (https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5). Format as a concise morning summary with emoji and send via message tool to Telegram target 1087368827.\nCurrent time: Wednesday, February 18th, 2026 — 7:00 AM (Asia/Singapore)"}],"timestamp":1771369200160}}
{"type":"message","id":"0b7e466b","parentId":"68e940a4","timestamp":"2026-02-17T23:01:01.583Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to send a daily ping message to Telegram with:\n1. Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API\n2. Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance\n3. Top 5 GitHub repos by stars\n\nLet me fetch this data and send it to Telegram target 1087368827.\n\nI'll need to:\n1. Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\n2. Get stock prices using yfinance (I'll need to use Python for this)\n3. Fetch top GitHub repos\n4. Format everything nicely\n5. Send to Telegram\n\nLet me start by fetching the Bitcoin and GitHub data via web_fetch, and use exec to run Python for y","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I'll fetch the Bitcoin price, stock data, and top GitHub repos,"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:0","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport yfinance as yf\nstocks = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nfor ticker in stocks:\n    try:\n        stock = yf.Ticker(ticker)\n        hist = stock.history(period='2d')\n        if len(hist) >= 2:\n            current = hist['Close'].iloc[-1]\n            prev = hist['Close'].iloc[-2]\n            change = ((current - prev) / prev) * 100\n            print(f'{ticker}: ${current:.2f} ({change:+.2f}%)')\n        else:\n            current = hist['Close'].iloc[-1]\n            print(f'{ticker}: ${current:.2f}')\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f'{ticker}: Error - {e}')\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":9415,"output":478,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9893,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771369200163}}
